1
00:00:00,400 --> 00:00:01,500
<i> Emil Padua.</i>

2
00:00:01,533 --> 00:00:03,367
<i>He will be transferred
to police custody today.</i>

3
00:00:03,367 --> 00:00:05,233
<i> I hope the others too</i>

4
00:00:05,233 --> 00:00:06,333
<i> get captured.</i>

5
00:00:06,333 --> 00:00:07,367
<i> As well as Greta Roja.</i>

6
00:00:07,367 --> 00:00:10,300
<i>I know Liam is in so much pain
right now.</i>

7
00:00:10,300 --> 00:00:12,500
<i>He still loves his mother
so much.</i>

8
00:00:12,500 --> 00:00:15,433
Please forgive me for everything
<i> I have done to you.</i>

9
00:00:15,433 --> 00:00:17,733
<i>So you've always wanted
to get rid of me.</i>

10
00:00:17,733 --> 00:00:19,600
<i> You ordered them yourself</i>

11
00:00:19,600 --> 00:00:21,533
<i> to not hurt anyone</i>

12
00:00:22,367 --> 00:00:23,667
<i> except for me.</i>

13
00:00:23,667 --> 00:00:26,733
"Just give the hostages a scare.

14
00:00:26,733 --> 00:00:28,400
<i> Don't hurt them.</i>

15
00:00:29,267 --> 00:00:31,467
<i> Except for one person."</i>

16
00:00:31,467 --> 00:00:34,467
Then I was shown a photo of you.

17
00:00:34,500 --> 00:00:36,433
<i> Don't hurt anyone?</i>

18
00:00:36,433 --> 00:00:38,200
<i> Except for me?!</i>

19
00:00:38,200 --> 00:00:39,167
<i> Why?</i>

20
00:00:39,167 --> 00:00:40,567
<i> Not out of anger,</i>

21
00:00:40,567 --> 00:00:42,300
<i> but out of fear.</i>

22
00:00:42,300 --> 00:00:44,267
<i> Magnus still loves you.</i>

23
00:00:44,267 --> 00:00:46,067
<i> You are my true...</i>

24
00:00:46,667 --> 00:00:48,267
<i> rival.</i>

25
00:00:48,267 --> 00:00:50,067
<i>You're not the only one
responsible.</i>

26
00:00:50,067 --> 00:00:51,500
<i> What do you mean?</i>

27
00:00:51,500 --> 00:00:54,033
I know I need to get jailed too.

28
00:00:54,033 --> 00:00:55,233
<i> No.</i>

29
00:00:55,233 --> 00:00:57,267
<i> You can't go to jail.</i>

30
00:00:57,267 --> 00:00:58,567
<i> For Liam's sake.</i>

31
00:00:58,767 --> 00:01:01,033
Can we not surrender my mom yet?

32
00:01:01,033 --> 00:01:02,633
<i> A lot of people died, Liam.</i>

33
00:01:02,633 --> 00:01:03,700
<i> I know.</i>

34
00:01:03,700 --> 00:01:06,500
<i>But can you let me spend
some time with her?</i>

35
00:01:06,500 --> 00:01:08,700
It'll be our last meal together.

36
00:01:08,733 --> 00:01:09,733
<i> Son...</i>

37
00:01:11,500 --> 00:01:12,600
<i> I'm ready.</i>

38
00:01:13,300 --> 00:01:16,100
<i>I have a deal
with General Cabral.</i>

39
00:01:16,100 --> 00:01:17,767
<i> He said I'll get protection,</i>

40
00:01:17,767 --> 00:01:20,467
<i>then why are you throwing me
to jail with his bastard?!</i>

41
00:01:20,467 --> 00:01:22,400
<i> You're both bastards, Jacinto.</i>

42
00:01:22,400 --> 00:01:23,400
<i> You are a policeman.</i>

43
00:01:23,400 --> 00:01:26,467
<i>You swore an oath,
but what did you do?</i>

44
00:01:29,567 --> 00:01:31,333
<i> We need to get Boss Emil.</i>

45
00:01:31,733 --> 00:01:33,633
<i>We'll get your father back,
Leni.</i>

46
00:01:34,500 --> 00:01:37,733
<i>We'll help him get
what he truly wants.</i>

47
00:01:40,867 --> 00:01:47,800
- [POLICE SIREN WAILING]
- [TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

48
00:02:01,600 --> 00:02:06,767
[FOREBODING MUSIC PLAYING]

49
00:02:06,767 --> 00:02:13,700
[POLICE SIREN WAILING]

50
00:02:25,500 --> 00:02:32,433
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]

51
00:03:05,767 --> 00:03:08,400
[OLSEN]<i> Your mother's lies
</i> are different.

52
00:03:08,400 --> 00:03:09,767
<i> A lot of people died, Liam.</i>

53
00:03:11,333 --> 00:03:12,600
[LIAM] I know.

54
00:03:14,200 --> 00:03:16,800
[GRETA CRYING]<i> Wait, Liam,
</i> I beg you.

55
00:03:16,800 --> 00:03:20,300
<i> I beg you, have mercy on me.</i>

56
00:03:20,300 --> 00:03:22,733
[GRETA CRYING]

57
00:03:22,767 --> 00:03:24,633
<i> Do you not love me anymore?</i>

58
00:03:24,633 --> 00:03:31,533
- [POIGNANT MUSIC PLAYING]
- [GRETA CRYING]

59
00:03:38,533 --> 00:03:40,800
<i>I'm turning you over
to the police</i>

60
00:03:40,800 --> 00:03:42,500
<i>because it's the right thing
to do.</i>

61
00:03:45,367 --> 00:03:47,600
[LIAM]<i> Can you give me
</i> some time to be with her?

62
00:03:48,367 --> 00:03:49,567
<i> Just for the last time.</i>

63
00:03:49,567 --> 00:03:53,300
[POIGNANT MUSIC CONTINUES]

64
00:03:53,300 --> 00:03:55,233
It'll be our last meal together.

65
00:03:55,267 --> 00:03:58,333
<i> Me, Mama, and Papa.</i>

66
00:04:05,500 --> 00:04:09,333
My signature, Tuna Wellington
in Espagnole sauce.

67
00:04:13,867 --> 00:04:15,200
[MAGNUS] Hmm!

68
00:04:17,600 --> 00:04:18,767
Enjoy!

69
00:04:19,833 --> 00:04:20,767
Thank you.

70
00:04:21,500 --> 00:04:22,833
It looks beautiful.

71
00:04:27,500 --> 00:04:30,733
I remember Nana Conching,

72
00:04:30,767 --> 00:04:31,933
your grandmother.

73
00:04:32,933 --> 00:04:35,333
She's an excellent cook too.

74
00:04:35,900 --> 00:04:38,500
Good thing you take after her.

75
00:04:38,500 --> 00:04:44,600
[POIGNANT MUSIC CONTINUES]

76
00:04:45,633 --> 00:04:46,767
<i> What is this?</i>

77
00:04:47,667 --> 00:04:48,633
<i> Huh?</i>

78
00:04:49,433 --> 00:04:51,433
<i> A full scholarship at a...</i>

79
00:04:52,633 --> 00:04:54,700
<i>A culinary school
in New York?</i>

80
00:04:55,967 --> 00:04:56,900
<i> Yes.</i>

81
00:04:57,667 --> 00:04:59,400
<i> Only two people passed.</i>

82
00:04:59,833 --> 00:05:01,000
<i> I'm the only Filipino.</i>

83
00:05:01,767 --> 00:05:03,767
<i> I did well on the exams.</i>

84
00:05:07,600 --> 00:05:08,667
<i> Wait.</i>

85
00:05:09,900 --> 00:05:11,967
<i> Help me understand all of this</i>

86
00:05:11,967 --> 00:05:15,067
<i> because I'm ignorant
to these things.</i> [LAUGHS]

87
00:05:15,067 --> 00:05:16,633
<i> Uh...</i>

88
00:05:17,567 --> 00:05:22,467
[MOCKINGLY]<i> What exactly
</i> is difficult about cooking?

89
00:05:22,467 --> 00:05:23,533
<i> Hmm?</i>

90
00:05:25,600 --> 00:05:27,667
[SLURPING, HUMMING]

91
00:05:27,667 --> 00:05:29,267
<i> Huh? What?</i>

92
00:05:31,567 --> 00:05:36,467
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

93
00:05:36,500 --> 00:05:37,833
I'm sorry, son.

94
00:05:38,967 --> 00:05:40,433
Your father's a fool.

95
00:05:41,033 --> 00:05:42,467
I, uhm...

96
00:05:43,100 --> 00:05:45,900
I looked down on your passion
for cooking

97
00:05:45,900 --> 00:05:48,300
but this is to die for.

98
00:05:49,433 --> 00:05:52,067
And I promise from here on in

99
00:05:52,067 --> 00:05:57,067
that I will support your passion
all the way, 100 percent.

100
00:05:57,833 --> 00:05:59,100
You gave your word.

101
00:05:59,100 --> 00:06:01,000
Yes. Yes, of course.

102
00:06:01,867 --> 00:06:04,067
I plan on pursuing my dreams.

103
00:06:04,067 --> 00:06:06,600
To study culinary in New York?

104
00:06:06,600 --> 00:06:10,633
- [CUTLERY CLINGING]
- [CHEWING]

105
00:06:10,667 --> 00:06:11,767
Nope.

106
00:06:12,967 --> 00:06:14,600
- Not anymore.
- [MAGNUS] Hmm?

107
00:06:17,400 --> 00:06:19,500
I'll bring La Playa Roja
back to life.

108
00:06:19,500 --> 00:06:20,667
[MAGNUS SCOFFS]

109
00:06:21,567 --> 00:06:23,867
I will open a new restaurant
at the resort.

110
00:06:25,733 --> 00:06:28,067
I know how important it is
for our family.

111
00:06:28,967 --> 00:06:30,600
Of course I wanted to do it too.

112
00:06:31,700 --> 00:06:33,800
Yes, a lot has happened.

113
00:06:34,900 --> 00:06:37,467
But Olsen and I have
more good memories there,

114
00:06:37,467 --> 00:06:38,767
all of us do.

115
00:06:38,767 --> 00:06:40,467
- Right, bro?
- [OLSEN CHUCKLES]

116
00:06:40,500 --> 00:06:44,167
[POIGNANT MUSIC PLAYING]

117
00:06:44,167 --> 00:06:45,200
<i> Ho!</i>

118
00:06:45,200 --> 00:06:48,933
- [OLSEN GRUNTING]
- [LIAM PUFFING]

119
00:06:48,933 --> 00:06:50,000
<i> Ha!</i>

120
00:06:51,567 --> 00:06:53,367
[BLOWS LANDING]

121
00:06:56,467 --> 00:06:57,433
[BLOW LANDS WEAKLY]

122
00:06:59,733 --> 00:07:01,000
[BLOW LANDS]

123
00:07:01,000 --> 00:07:01,933
[LIAM] Ah!

124
00:07:02,833 --> 00:07:04,133
<i>- Ah...
- One-zero!</i>

125
00:07:05,500 --> 00:07:08,900
<i>- Okay!
- Always keep your elbows in.</i>

126
00:07:08,900 --> 00:07:10,767
<i> Again. Move!</i>

127
00:07:10,767 --> 00:07:13,500
[BOTH GRUNTING] Hoo! Ha!

128
00:07:13,500 --> 00:07:15,500
[POIGNANT MUSIC CONTINUES]

129
00:07:15,533 --> 00:07:18,667
- [BLOW LANDS]
- [OLSEN GRUNTING]

130
00:07:18,667 --> 00:07:19,800
<i> One-one.</i>

131
00:07:19,800 --> 00:07:21,033
<i> Focus on the eye!</i>

132
00:07:21,033 --> 00:07:23,867
<i> - Ha!</i> [PUFFING]
- Ha!

133
00:07:26,033 --> 00:07:29,700
- [LIAM PUFFING]
- [OLSEN] Ha!

134
00:07:29,700 --> 00:07:30,800
[OLSEN] Argh!

135
00:07:31,867 --> 00:07:32,867
[LIAM] Ha!

136
00:07:34,200 --> 00:07:35,767
- [THUDS]
- [OLSEN PUFFS]

137
00:07:38,500 --> 00:07:39,633
<i> Two-one!</i>

138
00:07:39,633 --> 00:07:44,800
[POIGNANT MUSIC CONTINUES]

139
00:07:44,800 --> 00:07:46,533
[OLSEN GROANING] Why?!

140
00:07:46,533 --> 00:07:48,067
<i> We're tied now, bro.</i>

141
00:07:51,200 --> 00:07:52,967
A lot of mischief, you mean?

142
00:07:52,967 --> 00:07:56,000
[LAUGHTER]

143
00:07:58,900 --> 00:08:05,833
- [POLICE SIREN WAILING]
- [SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

144
00:08:12,733 --> 00:08:13,833
Cheers!

145
00:08:14,600 --> 00:08:15,667
To family.

146
00:08:17,667 --> 00:08:19,067
For the Roja family.

147
00:08:19,933 --> 00:08:25,833
[GLASSES CLINKING]

148
00:08:25,867 --> 00:08:32,800
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

149
00:08:33,700 --> 00:08:40,633
[GRIM MUSIC PLAYING]

150
00:08:50,867 --> 00:08:55,867
- [POLICE SIREN WAILING]
- [OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYING]

151
00:08:55,900 --> 00:08:57,800
I'm impressed, Jacinto.

152
00:08:58,533 --> 00:09:00,533
You got shot.

153
00:09:00,533 --> 00:09:02,267
Fell off a building.

154
00:09:02,267 --> 00:09:04,033
But you're still alive.

155
00:09:04,033 --> 00:09:06,133
[OMINOUS MUSIC CONTINUES]

156
00:09:06,133 --> 00:09:08,800
Let's see if you can get
through this.

157
00:09:08,800 --> 00:09:15,767
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

158
00:09:26,100 --> 00:09:31,833
- [TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]
- [POLICE SIREN WAILING]

159
00:09:38,500 --> 00:09:42,400
[WATER RUNNING]

160
00:09:42,400 --> 00:09:43,467
Wendy?

161
00:09:44,433 --> 00:09:45,500
[PLATE CLANGS]

162
00:09:46,367 --> 00:09:47,600
I'll help you.

163
00:09:47,600 --> 00:09:52,833
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]

164
00:09:52,833 --> 00:09:53,800
[GRETA] Back then,

165
00:09:54,633 --> 00:09:56,233
at the boarding house,

166
00:09:56,900 --> 00:09:58,567
I was so messy.

167
00:09:59,667 --> 00:10:00,833
[SIGHS]

168
00:10:00,833 --> 00:10:03,733
You're the one who cleans up
my mess.

169
00:10:05,433 --> 00:10:06,767
[PLATE CLANGS]

170
00:10:06,767 --> 00:10:08,267
How about now?

171
00:10:09,767 --> 00:10:12,233
You have no one to clean up
after you in prison.

172
00:10:13,967 --> 00:10:16,800
Do you want tips on how
to survive in there?

173
00:10:16,800 --> 00:10:23,733
[MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

174
00:10:24,733 --> 00:10:26,200
[BREATHES DEEPLY]

175
00:10:26,200 --> 00:10:27,367
Wendy...

176
00:10:29,900 --> 00:10:31,933
I'll leave my son in your care.

177
00:10:34,300 --> 00:10:35,333
[PLATE CLANGS]

178
00:10:37,667 --> 00:10:40,233
You don't have
to worry about Liam.

179
00:10:41,800 --> 00:10:43,500
You raised him right.

180
00:10:44,500 --> 00:10:45,867
Despite...

181
00:10:47,900 --> 00:10:49,800
Despite?

182
00:10:52,900 --> 00:10:54,567
How evil you are.

183
00:10:54,567 --> 00:11:01,500
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

184
00:11:16,333 --> 00:11:23,267
- [POLICE SIREN WAILING]
- [OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYING]

185
00:11:24,500 --> 00:11:26,367
[TIRES TEAR]

186
00:11:26,367 --> 00:11:27,500
An ambush!

187
00:11:28,600 --> 00:11:29,900
[TIRES TEARING]

188
00:11:29,900 --> 00:11:36,600
[CAR WHEELS SCREECHING]

189
00:11:36,600 --> 00:11:37,700
[GUNSHOT IN DISTANCE]

190
00:11:40,033 --> 00:11:46,967
[OMINOUS MUSIC CONTINUES]

191
00:11:53,333 --> 00:11:57,400
[SMOKE BOMBS THUDDING, HISSING]

192
00:12:00,367 --> 00:12:02,000
[SMOKE BOMB HISSING]

193
00:12:02,900 --> 00:12:04,433
[RAPID GUNFIRE]

194
00:12:04,433 --> 00:12:11,367
[SMOKE BOMBS HISSING]

195
00:12:16,533 --> 00:12:18,533
- [GUNSHOT]
- [FLESH RIPS]

196
00:12:18,533 --> 00:12:19,867
[THUDS]

197
00:12:21,733 --> 00:12:23,600
- [CAR DOOR SLIDES OPEN]
- [POLICEMEN] Get out! Get out!

198
00:12:23,600 --> 00:12:26,333
[POLICEMEN COUGHING]

199
00:12:26,333 --> 00:12:27,467
[POLICEMAN 1] My eyes sting!

200
00:12:28,433 --> 00:12:29,667
[CAR DOOR OPENS]

201
00:12:34,433 --> 00:12:36,067
[CAR DOOR SLIDES CLOSE]

202
00:12:36,067 --> 00:12:41,900
- [TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]
- [POLICEMEN COUGHING]

203
00:12:41,900 --> 00:12:43,333
[CAR DOOR CLOSES]

204
00:12:44,367 --> 00:12:46,833
[LEAVES RUSTLING]

205
00:12:50,900 --> 00:12:52,467
[CAR DOOR OPENS]

206
00:12:55,567 --> 00:13:02,533
- [RAPID GUNFIRE]
- [BULLETS RICOCHETING]

207
00:13:02,533 --> 00:13:09,533
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

208
00:13:09,533 --> 00:13:16,467
- [RAPID GUNFIRE]
- [BULLETS RICOCHETING]

209
00:13:23,167 --> 00:13:24,867
[GUN COCKS]

210
00:13:29,000 --> 00:13:32,967
- [RAPID GUNFIRE]
- [BULLETS RICOCHETING]

211
00:13:32,967 --> 00:13:39,900
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

212
00:13:47,667 --> 00:13:48,867
[RAPID GUNFIRE]

213
00:13:53,300 --> 00:13:57,167
[BIRDS CHIRPING]

214
00:13:57,200 --> 00:14:04,000
[MELANCHOLIC MUSIC PLAYING]

215
00:14:09,967 --> 00:14:11,000
[GRUNTS]

216
00:14:12,467 --> 00:14:13,633
[EXHALES DEEPLY]

217
00:14:18,933 --> 00:14:19,933
Wow.

218
00:14:20,467 --> 00:14:21,633
Thank you, Liam.

219
00:14:22,200 --> 00:14:24,133
I think that was the best meal
of my life.

220
00:14:24,133 --> 00:14:25,333
[LAUGHS]

221
00:14:26,033 --> 00:14:27,233
Full?

222
00:14:27,233 --> 00:14:28,267
Very full.

223
00:14:28,300 --> 00:14:30,333
- Missed my cooking?
- Ah...

224
00:14:31,167 --> 00:14:32,400
No, not really.

225
00:14:32,400 --> 00:14:34,267
[LAUGHTER]

226
00:14:34,267 --> 00:14:35,400
There'll be more.

227
00:14:36,133 --> 00:14:38,533
At the new restaurant
of La Playa Roja.

228
00:14:40,267 --> 00:14:42,667
It's such a shame that Mama
wouldn't be there to see it.

229
00:14:45,100 --> 00:14:46,367
[EXHALES HEAVILY]

230
00:14:47,700 --> 00:14:49,600
<i>You shouldn't be
the only one responsible.</i>

231
00:14:51,133 --> 00:14:52,467
<i> What do you mean?</i>

232
00:14:55,233 --> 00:14:56,367
<i> I know.</i>

233
00:14:57,933 --> 00:15:00,300
<i>I know that I need
to be jailed too.</i>

234
00:15:00,300 --> 00:15:05,000
[MELANCHOLIC MUSIC PLAYING]

235
00:15:05,033 --> 00:15:05,967
<i> No.</i>

236
00:15:06,500 --> 00:15:08,100
<i> You can't go to jail.</i>

237
00:15:09,167 --> 00:15:10,567
<i> For Liam's sake.</i>

238
00:15:11,967 --> 00:15:13,633
More than your commitment to me

239
00:15:15,100 --> 00:15:18,000
<i> is your commitment to our son.</i>

240
00:15:19,300 --> 00:15:21,300
I'm sorry for everything, son.

241
00:15:21,300 --> 00:15:27,633
[MELANCHOLIC MUSIC CONTINUES]

242
00:15:27,633 --> 00:15:29,267
All is forgiven, Pa.

243
00:15:30,100 --> 00:15:31,500
We'll start anew.

244
00:15:32,733 --> 00:15:34,200
Start anew.

245
00:15:35,700 --> 00:15:37,033
Thank you.

246
00:15:37,033 --> 00:15:44,000
[MELANCHOLIC MUSIC CONTINUES]

247
00:15:50,200 --> 00:15:55,500
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

248
00:15:55,500 --> 00:16:02,433
- [RAPID GUNFIRE]
- [BULLETS RICOCHETING]

249
00:16:05,200 --> 00:16:08,133
[RAPID GUNFIRE]

250
00:16:08,167 --> 00:16:13,033
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

251
00:16:13,033 --> 00:16:14,000
